<br>
Now, since that time, Brad, the driving force behind the TLC, is gone. And the TLC has been removed from all zones on all other servers, so there is now virtually no incentive to fix any prolems that arise, nor is their an in-house champion for the cause. There certainly is virtually no reason for them to spend the time to research potential TLC problems in designing future zones and quests.<br>
<br>
Those are fairly large changes. It's like you go to the store and buy WIndows XP and the very next day Microsoft releases a completely different OS and says that XP is no longer supported and any bugs or problems with it will never be fixed. If your video card doesn't work, well, that's tough, figure out a way to 'work around it'. If your hard drive loses data, well, bummer, no longer supported.<br>
<br>
What we have - a buggy unsupported TLC with a myriad of problems - is far different than what we should have expected. Sure, I expected problems with it, such a drastic change to all zones and quests, most of which predate the idea behind the TLC. And that was fine, because I had some rerason to believe that problems would actually be addressed, changes made as needed where there were obvious problems. But...that is no longer the case.<br>
<br>
They call that 'bait and switch' where I come from: offer you an item to lure you into the store, then tell you they are out of that item but instead they are more than happy to sell you this other item (generally inferior, and certainly so in this case). And I *do* have a problem with bait-and-switch tactics, personally.<br>
<br>
Coriolis of Erudin, Firiona Vie, Illusionist<br>
